1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:41,860 --> 00:01:44,620
I've got to grab him and run!

3
00:01:47,100 --> 00:01:49,630
I should have enough stamina...

4
00:01:49,630 --> 00:01:50,960
Room!

5
00:01:55,130 --> 00:01:56,300
Shamb–

6
00:01:58,550 --> 00:02:00,880
I feel weak...!

7
00:02:03,430 --> 00:02:06,010
Stop what you're doing, Trafalgar.

8
00:02:07,310 --> 00:02:10,810
Not you again!

9
00:02:10,810 --> 00:02:16,020
The seastone used across
the world originated in Wano.

10
00:02:17,570 --> 00:02:20,570
A seastone... nail?!

11
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:26,330
Only the artisans of Wano are capable
of refining it into something that small.

12
00:02:28,370 --> 00:02:29,870
Straw Sword!

13
00:02:40,050 --> 00:02:43,010
Damn! This is bad...!

14
00:02:46,020 --> 00:02:47,220
Room!

15
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:49,970
Shambles!

16
00:02:52,270 --> 00:02:54,230
What an irritating ability...

17
00:02:57,940 --> 00:02:59,860
He can't have gotten far.

18
00:03:00,570 --> 00:03:03,550
He's nearby. Look for him!

19
00:03:03,550 --> 00:03:04,620
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

20
00:03:13,790 --> 00:03:15,520
Lock him up!

21
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:17,340
– Oh, y-yes, sir!
– Oh, y-yes, sir!

22
00:03:17,340 --> 00:03:21,190
Once we break his spirit, he'll fight for us!

23
00:03:21,190 --> 00:03:22,820
– Y-Yes, sir!
– Y-Yes, sir!

24
00:03:22,820 --> 00:03:25,740
Don't mention the word "pirate"
in the notice papers.

25
00:03:25,740 --> 00:03:27,010
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

26
00:03:27,640 --> 00:03:34,400
I can't have the moronic populace getting even
the tiniest bit curious about the outside world.

27
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:35,320
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

28
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:36,670
Let's take him!

29
00:03:36,670 --> 00:03:39,320
Hey, guys grab his feet!

30
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:40,150
– Right!
– Right!

31
00:04:05,430 --> 00:04:07,390
You have it, too?!

32
00:04:07,390 --> 00:04:09,930
Damn punk!

33
00:04:12,390 --> 00:04:14,190
No way!

34
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:19,900
That was Lord Oden's technique!

35
00:04:20,470 --> 00:04:24,030
He can even do it while unconscious?!

36
00:04:26,330 --> 00:04:30,290
Who the hell is that brat?!

37
00:04:34,500 --> 00:04:37,340
That brat Kid uses conqueror's haki, too!

38
00:04:37,340 --> 00:04:40,920
As if we even need...

39
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:43,670
any more conquerors!

40
00:04:58,090 --> 00:05:01,000
I'll deal with Trafalgar later.

41
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,690
Time to get back to drinking.

42
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:11,620
Now I'm completely sober.

43
00:05:52,710 --> 00:05:55,670
A seastone nail?

44
00:05:55,670 --> 00:05:58,790
I've never even heard of that before.

45
00:06:00,670 --> 00:06:02,090
This is bad.

46
00:06:02,090 --> 00:06:04,670
– Captain!
– Captain!

47
00:06:05,780 --> 00:06:08,760
I hope Bepo and the others are okay.

48
00:06:14,930 --> 00:06:16,610
Hawkins, sir!

49
00:06:16,610 --> 00:06:18,730
Did you find Trafalgar?

50
00:06:18,730 --> 00:06:23,000
Well, we looked all over
but he's nowhere to be found!

51
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:26,560
He must've already left town.

52
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,780
Cuff him!

53
00:06:29,780 --> 00:06:31,030
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

54
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:43,040
That we caught Straw Hat is enough for now...

55
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:48,300
But I swear I'll track you down,
too, Trafalgar Law!

56
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:50,570
I won't let him get away!

57
00:06:55,990 --> 00:06:57,520
Mr. Gorobe!

58
00:06:57,520 --> 00:06:59,140
Hey, stay with us!

59
00:07:02,540 --> 00:07:05,080
I'll treat you right away.

60
00:07:07,870 --> 00:07:10,000
I think that voice belongs to...

61
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:12,340
I want to apologize...

62
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:17,620
I want to apologize to Luffytaro.

63
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:24,080
He took the trouble to bring us food,
but it went to waste...!

64
00:07:24,080 --> 00:07:26,720
Do not pay that any mind.

65
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:31,930
I just hope he doesn't feel responsible
for the town getting attacked.

66
00:07:33,150 --> 00:07:35,930
He is such a kind man...

67
00:07:38,370 --> 00:07:42,730
Still beautiful after twenty years!
She hasn't changed a bit!

68
00:07:43,030 --> 00:07:49,540
Still, I can only see you again
once I have fulfilled Lord Oden's dream!

69
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:54,570
Forgive me for being such a selfish husband!

70
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:09,860
That's...

71
00:08:10,140 --> 00:08:12,020
Ashura Doji!

72
00:08:19,970 --> 00:08:21,890
A massive hole?!

73
00:08:21,890 --> 00:08:23,810
Okiku!

74
00:08:26,770 --> 00:08:28,110
Don't tell me...!

75
00:08:33,570 --> 00:08:37,990
Help us! A big sinkhole opened up!

76
00:08:37,990 --> 00:08:39,870
Okiku my darling!

77
00:08:39,870 --> 00:08:42,410
We managed to survive!

78
00:08:42,410 --> 00:08:44,540
– Hey!
– We're here!

79
00:08:44,540 --> 00:08:45,790
Thank goodness!

80
00:08:45,790 --> 00:08:48,840
You are all safe!

81
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:52,210
The sinkhole saved us but...

82
00:08:53,190 --> 00:08:55,090
We're falling!

83
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:57,180
Everyone!

84
00:08:59,030 --> 00:09:00,390
Oh dear!

85
00:09:00,390 --> 00:09:02,360
Hold on tight!

86
00:09:06,140 --> 00:09:07,890
– Thank you!
– Thank you!

87
00:09:07,890 --> 00:09:09,570
My hero!

88
00:09:14,130 --> 00:09:16,860
I managed to rescue the ladies!

89
00:09:16,860 --> 00:09:21,130
– Why didn't you save us, too?!
– Why didn't you save us, too?!

90
00:09:21,130 --> 00:09:23,910
It was a close call!

91
00:09:23,910 --> 00:09:28,660
So Shino's technique saved
everyone in the nick of time!

92
00:09:28,660 --> 00:09:30,380
That's right!

93
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:33,590
At that moment...

94
00:09:33,590 --> 00:09:36,390
Blast Breath!

95
00:09:45,450 --> 00:09:48,400
Ripe-Ripe Seduction Technique!

96
00:09:56,790 --> 00:09:58,870
Guard Point!

97
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:20,610
We made it!

98
00:10:24,070 --> 00:10:31,190
My Ripe-Ripe Seduction Technique
can make anything more mature!

99
00:10:31,190 --> 00:10:35,110
Yes! Shino can rot anything with a touch!

100
00:10:35,110 --> 00:10:37,190
Rot...! Don't say it like that!

101
00:10:37,190 --> 00:10:40,400
Anyway, about our situation...

102
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:41,620
Oh, yeah!

103
00:10:41,620 --> 00:10:43,570
What happened to Luffy?!

104
00:10:43,570 --> 00:10:46,820
He looked like he wanted to
pick a fight with Kaido!

105
00:10:49,390 --> 00:10:51,540
Brace yourselves and listen closely.

106
00:11:08,820 --> 00:11:11,440
How could he do something so cruel?!

107
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:13,680
She's still breathing!

108
00:11:13,680 --> 00:11:15,440
Help her!

109
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:16,420
Yes, sir!

110
00:11:17,030 --> 00:11:19,720
People can see us here,
so let's go into the forest!

111
00:11:21,250 --> 00:11:23,910
That he'd even harm children...!

112
00:11:33,790 --> 00:11:37,500
Damn you, Kaido!

113
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:05,410
News of Luffytaro's big fight in Kuri...

114
00:12:05,410 --> 00:12:07,760
Extra! Extra!

115
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:12,370
Read all about it! Extra! Extra!

116
00:12:14,470 --> 00:12:17,590
...spread across Wano.

117
00:12:26,900 --> 00:12:29,010
Hm? Is this a notice paper?

118
00:12:30,230 --> 00:12:32,550
Oh! Luffy!

119
00:12:32,550 --> 00:12:34,570
So he's here in Wa–

120
00:12:56,270 --> 00:12:57,500
Oh, Luffy!

121
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:59,170
So here's here in–

122
00:13:10,860 --> 00:13:13,140
Extra! Extra!

123
00:13:13,980 --> 00:13:14,850
Lu–

124
00:13:40,930 --> 00:13:42,600
It burns!

125
00:13:54,020 --> 00:13:55,720
Hmm...

126
00:13:55,720 --> 00:14:00,410
It's hard to believe such a wild rogue
has shown up in Wano.

127
00:14:01,410 --> 00:14:03,270
What're you reading?

128
00:14:03,270 --> 00:14:04,030
It burns!

129
00:14:04,030 --> 00:14:08,110
Oh, a samurai named Luffytaro
fought Lord Kaido.

130
00:14:12,530 --> 00:14:15,070
Whoa! That's disgusting, bro!

131
00:14:15,070 --> 00:14:17,370
Don't spew out wasabi sushi!

132
00:14:17,370 --> 00:14:21,030
And you ate too much!
Can you pay for it all?!

133
00:14:21,030 --> 00:14:22,670
Let me see that!

134
00:14:29,610 --> 00:14:32,390
What are you doing, Luffy?!

135
00:14:46,830 --> 00:14:49,950
Beat, beat! Beat the iron flat!

136
00:14:52,420 --> 00:14:57,410
The harder and stronger the weapons
we create, the more the capital will flourish!

137
00:14:57,410 --> 00:15:00,340
Your lives belong to Shogun Orochi!

138
00:15:00,930 --> 00:15:02,920
If you wanna live, beat the iron flat!

139
00:15:02,920 --> 00:15:06,470
If you wanna rest, I'll kill you!

140
00:15:07,100 --> 00:15:09,470
Move faster!

141
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:12,770
Wano's Udon region...

142
00:15:12,770 --> 00:15:16,650
is home to the weapons factories and mines...

143
00:15:16,690 --> 00:15:20,940
in which prisoners are forced to work.

144
00:15:25,450 --> 00:15:27,980
Here you go! Poisonous fish!

145
00:15:31,460 --> 00:15:34,770
What's in this cell anyway?

146
00:15:34,770 --> 00:15:36,290
Dunno...

147
00:15:36,290 --> 00:15:42,420
I was told to throw in one poisonous fish
each day after removing the bones.

148
00:15:42,420 --> 00:15:43,630
That's all.

149
00:15:43,630 --> 00:15:47,840
That means it likes poisonous fish?

150
00:15:47,840 --> 00:15:51,840
Typically, they feed poisonous fish
as a method of execution.

151
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:58,800
But whatever's in this cell eats them anyway
and just stubbornly goes on living.

152
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:01,350
Is it a shark or a crocodile or something?

153
00:16:01,350 --> 00:16:06,690
Why do we have to bother removing
the bones? It's a pain in the ass!

154
00:16:07,570 --> 00:16:08,980
That's because...

155
00:16:13,310 --> 00:16:14,740
"Heinous criminal"?!

156
00:16:14,990 --> 00:16:20,120
That means the new guy
everyone is talking about just arrived!

157
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:21,290
What?!

158
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:28,970
Welcome, new guy!

159
00:16:30,120 --> 00:16:31,720
You have a lot of nerve!

160
00:16:34,010 --> 00:16:37,680
You're as good as dead since
you messed with Viceroy Kaido!

161
00:16:39,930 --> 00:16:41,640
Get ready!

162
00:16:48,770 --> 00:16:51,190
Come on! Walk faster!

163
00:16:59,410 --> 00:17:01,580
Hey, is that really the guy...

164
00:17:01,580 --> 00:17:06,760
whose fight with Viceroy Kaido
devastated a town in Kuri?

165
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:08,380
I think so.

166
00:17:08,380 --> 00:17:09,690
That little guy?!

167
00:17:09,690 --> 00:17:14,090
Yeah, I thought he was at least
going to be huge like the Superstars!

168
00:17:14,090 --> 00:17:16,380
Hey, say something!

169
00:17:20,350 --> 00:17:22,290
He's so weak!

170
00:17:22,290 --> 00:17:26,740
Did this loser really challenge Viceroy Kaido?!

171
00:17:26,740 --> 00:17:30,450
Hey, no taking a break! Get up already!

172
00:17:38,780 --> 00:17:41,540
Huh? That's quite the look in his eyes!

173
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:50,460
That's fine. I'll take the time to
torture you until your eyes become dull!

174
00:17:54,260 --> 00:17:58,650
What's wrong with him?!
He's glaring at us prison guards!

175
00:18:01,140 --> 00:18:05,030
I'm gonna teach you what happens
when you defy us!

176
00:18:05,030 --> 00:18:06,100
Die!

177
00:18:14,900 --> 00:18:16,540
My neck!

178
00:18:16,540 --> 00:18:19,150
A fishbone came flying from the cell!

179
00:18:19,150 --> 00:18:22,580
Idiot! Didn't you remove
the bones before feeding it?!

180
00:18:22,580 --> 00:18:25,950
Ouch! My neck!

181
00:18:25,950 --> 00:18:29,200
What is it?! What's in this cell?!

182
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:30,770
No one knows!

183
00:18:36,220 --> 00:18:38,930
All right, you'll be staying here!

184
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:44,350
Until your spirit gets broken
and you bend the knee to Viceroy Kaido!

185
00:18:48,300 --> 00:18:51,110
Tomorrow is when we start
pushing you to the brink!

186
00:18:51,110 --> 00:18:53,500
We're gonna work you to the bone!

187
00:18:59,700 --> 00:19:03,250
All right then! Rest up today!

188
00:19:03,250 --> 00:19:05,960
Tomorrow's gonna be hell!

